<sc num="1" id="Mateo-1">
<cm>
<sv num="1" id="Mateo-1-1"/>
The book of the generation of Jesus 
<t lang="es"><st n="976">El libro </st><st n="1078">de la 
generación</st> <st n="2424">de Jesús</st> </t>
<rb>Christ
<t lang="es"><st n="5547">el Cristo</st></t><rf>Christ (Greek)
and Messiah (Hebrew) both mean «Anointed One»
<t lang="es">Cristo (griego) y Mesías (hebreo) ambos significan
«El ungido.»</t></rf>
</rb>
, the son of David, the son of Abraham. 
<t lang="es">, <st n="5207">el hijo</st><st n="1138">de David</st>, 
<st n="5207">el hijo</st> <st n="11">de Abraham</st>. </t>
<sv num="2" id="Mateo-1-2"/>
Abraham became the father of Isaac. Isaac became the father
of Jacob. Jacob became the father of Judah and his brothers. 
<t lang="es"><st n="11">Abraham</st> <st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> 
<st n="2464">Isaac</st>, <st n="1161">e</st> <st n="2464">Isaac</st> 
<st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> 
<st n="2384">Jacob</st>, <st n="1161">y</st> <st n="2384">Jacob</st> 
<st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> 
<st n="2455">Judá</st> <st n="2532">y</st> <st n="846">sus</st> 
<st n="80">hermanos</st>. </t>
<sv num="3" id="Mateo-1-3"/>
Judah
became the father of Perez and Zerah by Tamar. Perez became the father of
Hezron. Hezron became the father of Ram. 
<t lang="es"><st c="1161"></st> <st n="2455">Judá</st> <st n="1080">fue el 
padre de</st> <st n="5329">Fares</st> <st n="2532">y de</st> 
<st n="2196">Zara</st>, </t>
<rb lang="es"><st c="1537">la madre fue </st><rf><citebib id="KJV2003"/>
dice `de Tamar,´ <citebib id="Gideons"/> dice `con Tamar´</rf></rb>
<t lang="es"><st n="2283">Tamar</st>. <st n="1161">Y</st> 
<st n="5329">Fares</st> <st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> 
<st n="2074">Esrom</st>; 
<st c="1161"></st> <st n="2074">Esrom</st> <st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> 
<st n="689">Aram</st>. </t>
<sv num="4" id="Mateo-1-4"/>
Ram became the father of
Amminadab. Amminadab became the father of Nahshon. Nahshon became the father
of Salmon. 
<t lang="es"><st c="1161"></st> <st n="689">Aram</st> <st n="1080">fue el 
padre de</st> <st n="284">Aminadab</st>; <st n="1161">y</st> 
<st n="284">Aminadab</st> <st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> 
<st n="3476">Naasón</st>.
<st c="1161"></st> <st n="3476">Naasón</st> <st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> 
<st n="4533">Salmón</st>. </t>
<sv num="5" id="Mateo-1-5"/>
Salmon became the father of Boaz by Rahab. Boaz became the
father of Obed by Ruth. Obed became the father of Jesse. 
<t lang="es"><st c="1161"></st><st n="4533">Salmón</st> <st n="1080">fue el 
padre de</st> <st n="1003">Booz</st>, <st c="1537">la madre fue</st> 
<st n="4477">Rahab</st>.
<st c="1161"></st> <st n="1003">Booz</st> <st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> 
<st n="5601">Obed</st>, <st c="1537">la madre fue</st> <st n="4503">Rut</st>. 
<st c="1161"></st> <st n="5601">Obed</st> <st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> 
<st n="2421">Jessé</st>. </t>
<sv num="6" id="Mateo-1-6"/>
Jesse became
the father of David the king. David became the father of Solomon by her who
had been the wife of Uriah. 
<t lang="es"><st n="1161">Y</st> <st n="2421">Jessé</st> <st n="1080">fue el 
padre del</st> <st c="1138,935">rey David</st>. 
<st c="1161"></st> <st c="1138,935">El rey David</st> <st n="1080">fue el padre de</st>
<st n="4672">Salomón</st>, <st c="1537">la madre fue</st> <st n="3588">la que</st> 
<st c="3774">había sido esposa de Urias</st>. </t>
<sv num="7" id="Mateo-1-7"/>
Solomon became the father of Rehoboam.
Rehoboam became the father of Abijah. Abijah became the father of Asa.
<t lang="es"><st c="1161"></st> <st n="4672">Salomón</st> 
<st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> <st n="4497">Roboam</st>. 
<st c="1161"></st> <st n="4497">Roboam</st> <st n="1080">fue el padre de</st>
<st n="7">Abias</st>. <st c="1161"></st> <st n="7">Abias</st> 
<st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> <st n="760">Asa</st>. </t>
<sv num="8" id="Mateo-1-8"/>
Asa became the father of Jehoshaphat. Jehoshaphat became the father of
Joram. Joram became the father of Uzziah. 
<t lang="es"><st c="1161"></st> <st n="760">Asa</st> 
<st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> <st n="2498">Josafat</st>. 
<st c="1161"></st> <st n="2498">Josafat</st> <st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> 
<st n="2496">Joram</st>.
<st c="1161"></st> <st n="2496">Joram</st> <st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> 
<st n="3604">Uzias</st>. </t>
<sv num="9" id="Mateo-1-9"/>
Uzziah became the father of
Jotham. Jotham became the father of Ahaz. Ahaz became the father of Hezekiah.
<t lang="es"><st c="1161"></st> <st n="3604">Uzias</st> <st n="1080">fue el 
padre de</st> <st n="2488">Jotam</st>. <st c="1161"></st> <st n="2488">Jotam</st> 
<st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> <st n="881">Acaz</st>. 
<st c="1161"></st> <st n="881">Acaz</st> <st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> 
<st n="1478">Ezequias</st>. </t>
<sv num="10" id="Mateo-1-10"/>
Hezekiah became the father of Manasseh. Manasseh became the father of
Amon. Amon became the father of Josiah. 
<t lang="es"><st c="1161"></st> <st n="1478">Ezequias</st> 
<st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> 
<st n="3128">Manasés</st>. <st c="1161"></st> <st n="3128">Manasés</st> 
<st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> <st n="300">Amón</st>. <st c="1161"></st> 
<st n="300">Amón</st> <st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> 
<st n="2502">Josías</st>. </t>
<sv num="11" id="Mateo-1-11"/>
Josiah became the father of
Jechoniah and his brothers, at the time of the exile to Babylon. 
<t lang="es"><st c="1161"></st> <st n="2502">Josías</st> 
<st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> <st n="2423">Jeconías</st> 
<st n="2532">y</st> <st n="80">sus hermanos</st>, <st n="1909">en el tiempo</st>
que <st c="846"/> <st n="3350">fueron llevados</st> </t>
<rb lang="es">cautivos a <st n="897">Babilonia</st><rf><citebib id="WEB"/> dice `exilio,´ <citebib id="DieBibel"/> dice `prisión,´ <citebib id="DiosHablaHoy"/> dice `en el tiempo en que los israelitas fueron llevados cautivos a Babilonia,´  <citebib id="Peshitta"/> dice `cautiverio.´ <citebib id="KJV2003"/> dice
`en el tiempo que fueron llevados a Babilonia.´</rf></rb>
<t lang="es">. </t>
<sv num="12" id="Mateo-1-12"/>
After the exile to Babylon, Jechoniah became the father of Shealtiel. Shealtiel
became the father of Zerubbabel. 
<t lang="es"><st n="1161">Y</st> <st n="3326">después</st> de 
<st n="3350">que fueron llevados a</st> <st n="897">Babilonia</st>, 
<st n="2423">Jeconías</st> <st n="1080">fue el padre
de</st> <st n="4528">Salatiel</st>. <st c="1161"></st><st n="4528">Salatiel</st> 
<st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> <st n="2216">Zerobabel</st>. </t>
<sv num="13" id="Mateo-1-13"/>
Zerubbabel became the father of Abiud.
Abiud became the father of Eliakim. Eliakim became the father of Azor.
<t lang="es"><st c="1161"></st> <st n="2216">Zerobabel</st> 
<st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> <st n="10">Abiud</st>. 
<st c="1161"></st> <st n="10">Abiud</st> <st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> 
<st n="1662">Eliaquim</st>. <st c="1161"></st> <st n="1662">Eliaquim</st> 
<st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> <st n="107">Azor</st>. </t>
<sv num="14" id="Mateo-1-14"/>
Azor became the father of Sadoc. Sadoc became the father of Achim.
Achim became the father of Eliud. 
<t lang="es"><st c="1161"></st> <st n="107">Azor</st> 
<st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> 
<st n="4524">Sadoc</st>. <st c="1161"></st><st n="4524">Sadoc</st> 
<st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> <st n="885">Aquim</st>. 
<st c="1161"></st><st n="885">Aquim</st> <st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> 
<st n="1664">Eliud</st>. </t>
<sv num="15" id="Mateo-1-15"/>
Eliud became the father of Eleazar.
Eleazar became the father of Matthan. Matthan became the father of Jacob.
<t lang="es"><st c="1161"></st> <st n="1664">Eliud</st> 
<st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> <st n="1648">Eleazar</st>. 
<st c="1161"></st> <st n="1648">Eleazar</st> <st n="1080">fue el padre de</st>
<st n="3157">Matán</st>. <st c="1161"></st> <st n="3157">Matán</st> 
<st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> <st n="2384">Jacob</st>. </t>
<sv num="16" id="Mateo-1-16"/>
Jacob became the father of Joseph, the husband of Mary, from whom was
born 
<t lang="es"><st c="1161"></st> <st n="2384">Jacob</st> 
<st n="1080">fue el padre de</st> <st n="2501">José</st>, el 
<st n="435">esposo</st> de <st n="3137">Maria</st>, <st n="1537">de</st> 
<st n="3739">quien</st> <st n="1080">nació</st> </t> 
<rb>Jesus
<t lang="es"><st n="2424">Jesús</st></t>
<rf>«Jesus» is a Greek variant of the Jewish name «Yehoshua,»
which means «Yah saves.» «Jesus» is also the masculine form of «Yeshu`ah,»
which means «Salvation.»
<t lang="es">«Jesús» es una variación griega del nombre Judío
«Yehoshua,» que significa «Yah salva.» «Jesús» es también la
forma masculina de «Yeshu`ah,» que significa «Salvación.»</t></rf>
</rb>
, who is called Christ. 
<t lang="es">, <st n="3004">a quien se llama</st> <st n="5547">Cristo</st>. </t>
<sv num="17" id="Mateo-1-17"/>
So all the generations from Abraham to David are fourteen generations; from 
David to the exile to Babylon fourteen generations; and from the carrying 
away to Babylon to the Christ, fourteen generations.
<t lang="es"><st n="3767">Así que</st> <st n="3956">todas</st> 
<st n="1074">las generaciones</st> <st n="575">desde</st> 
<st n="11">Abraham</st> <st n="2193">hasta</st> <st n="1138">David</st> 
<st n="1180">son catorce</st><st n="1074"></st>; <st n="2532">y</st> 
<st n="575">desde</st> <st n="1138">David</st> <st n="2193">hasta</st> 
<st n="3350">que los llevaron a</st> <st n="897">Babilonia</st> 
<st n="1180">catorce</st> <st n="1074">generaciones</st>;
<st n="2532">y</st> <st n="575">desde</st> <st n="3350">que los llevaron a</st> 
<st n="897">Babilonia</st> <st n="2193">hasta</st> <st n="5547">Cristo</st>, 
<st n="1180">catorce</st> <st n="1074">generaciones</st>. </t>
</cm>
<cm>
<sv num="18" id="Mateo-1-18"/>
Now the birth of Jesus Christ was like this; for after his mother,
Mary, was engaged to Joseph, before they came together, she was found
pregnant by the Holy Spirit. 
<t lang="es"><st n="2228"></st><st c="1161"></st> <st n="1083">El nacimiento</st> 
de </t>
<rb lang="es"><st n="2424">Jesús</st> el <st n="5547">Cristo</st><rf>En 
<citebib id="NTG26"/> y en 
varias traducciones a otros idiomas (incluyendo <citebib id="WEB"/>) dice 
`Jesús Cristo,´ pero en español comunmente se usa `Jesús el Cristo´ o 
`Jesucristo.´ </rf></rb>
<t lang="es"> <st n="2258">fue</st> <st n="3779">así</st>: 
<st n="1063">después</st> de que <st n="846">su</st> <st n="3384">madre</st>, 
<st n="3137">Maria</st> se había <st n="3423">comprometido</st> 
con <st n="2501">José</st>, y <st n="4250">antes</st> de que <st n="846"></st>
estuvieran <st n="4905">juntos</st>,
<st n="2147">ella se encontró</st> <st c="2192,1064,1722">embarazada</st> 
<st n="1537">por</st> <st n="4151">el</st> 
<st c="40,4151">Espíritu Santo</st>. </t>
<sv num="19" id="Mateo-1-19"/>
Joseph, her husband, being a righteous
man, and not willing to make her a public example, intended to put her away
secretly. 
<t lang="es"><st n="1161">Entonces</st> <st n="2501">José</st>, 
<st n="846">su</st> <st n="435">marido</st>, <st n="5607">siendo</st> un 
hombre <st n="1342">justo</st>, <st n="2532">y</st> <st n="3361">no</st> 
<st n="2309">queriendo</st> <st n="3856">hacer</st> de <st n="846">ella</st> 
un <st n="3856">ejemplo público</st>, <st n="1014">quizo</st> </t>
<rb lang="es"><st c="630,846,630">separarse de ella</st><rf><citebib id="WEB"/> 
dice `separarla en secreto.´</rf></rb>
<t lang="es"> <st n="2977">en secreto</st>. </t>
<sv num="20" id="Mateo-1-20"/>
But when he thought about these things, behold, an angel of
the Lord appeared to him in a dream, saying, «Joseph, son of David, don´t be
afraid to take to yourself Mary, your wife, for that which is conceived in
her is of the Holy Spirit. 
<t lang="es"><st n="1161">Pero</st> <st n="1760">mientras</st><st n="846"/>
<st c="1760">pensaba</st> <st n="5023">estas cosas</st>, <st n="2400"></st> </t>
<rb lang="es"><st n="32">un ángel</st><rf><citebib id="KJV2003"/> dice
`el ángel,´ <citebib id="WEB"/> dice `un ángel.´</rf></rb> 
<t lang="es"><st n="2962">del Señor</st>
<st c="5316,846">se le apareció</st> <st n="2596">en</st> un 
<st n="3677">sueño</st>, <st n="3004">diciendo</st>, «<st n="2501">José</st>, 
<st n="5207">hijo</st> de <st n="1138">David</st>,
<st c="5399,3361">no temas</st> <st n="3880">tomar</st> a 
<st n="3137">María</st>, <st n="4675">tu</st> <st n="1135">esposa</st>, 
<st c="1063,3588">pues quien</st> se ha 
<st n="1080">concebido</st> <st n="1722">en</st> <st n="846">ella</st> 
<st n="2076">es</st> <st c="1537,4151">del</st> 
<st c="40,4151">Espíritu Santo</st>. </t>
<sv num="21" id="Mateo-1-21"/>
She shall bring forth a son. You shall call
his name Jesus, for it is he who shall save his people from their sins.»
<t lang="es"><st c="1161"/> <st n="5088">Ella dará a luz</st> un 
<st n="5207">hijo</st>. <st c="2532"/> <st c="2564,846,3686">Debes 
llamarlo</st> <st n="2424">Jesús</st>, <st n="1063">porque</st> 
<st n="846">Él</st> es quien <st n="4982">salvará</st> a <st n="846">su</st> 
<st n="2992">gente</st> <st n="575">de</st> <st n="846">sus</st> 
<st n="266">pecados</st>.» </t>
</cm>
<cm>
<sv num="22" id="Mateo-1-22"/>
Now all this has happened, that it might be fulfilled which was spoken
by the Lord through the prophet, saying,
<t lang="es"><st c="1161"/> <st n="3650">Todo</st> <st n="5124">esto</st> </t>
<rb lang="es"><st n="1096">fue hecho</st><rf><citebib id="WEB"/> dice 
`ocurrió,´ <citebib id="KJV2003"/> dice `fue hecho.´</rf></rb>
<t lang="es">, <st n="2443">para que</st> se <st n="4137">cumpliera</st> 
<st n="3588">lo que</st> <st n="4483">fue dicho</st> 
<st n="5259">por</st> <st n="2962">el Señor</st> <st n="1223">por medio</st> 
del <st n="4396">profeta</st> que <st n="3004">dijo</st></t>
<pp><cm>
</cm>
<cm>
<sv num="23" id="Mateo-1-23"/>
«Behold, the virgin shall be with child,
<t lang="es">«<st n="2400">Observen</st>, la <st n="3933">virgen</st> </t>
<rb lang="es"><st c="2192,1722">concebirá</st><rf><citebib id="WEB"/> 
y <citebib id="KJV2003"/> dicen `estará con niño,´ <citebib id="Peshitta"/> 
dice `concebirá.´</rf></rb>
<t lang="es"> un <st n="1064">niño</st>, </t>
<cl/>
And shall bring forth a son.
<t lang="es"><st n="2532">y</st> <st n="5088">dará a luz</st> 
un <st n="5207">hijo</st>. </t>
</cm>
<cm>
They shall call his name Immanuel;»
<t lang="es"><st n="2532">Y</st> </t>
<rb lang="es"><st c="2564,846,3686">lo llamaran</st><rf><citebib id="WEB"/> y 
<citebib id="KJV2003"/> dicen `llamarán su nombre.´</rf></rb>
<t lang="es"> <st n="1694">Emmanuel</st>;» </t>
<cl/>
Which is, being interpreted, «God with us.»
<t lang="es"><st n="3739">que</st> <st n="3177">traducido</st> 
<st n="2076">es</st> «<st n="2316">Dios</st> <st n="3326">con</st> 
<st n="2257">nosotros</st>.» </t>
</cm>
</pp>
</cm>
<cm>

<t lang="es"></t>
<sv num="24" id="Mateo-1-24"/>
Joseph arose from his sleep, and did as the angel of the Lord commanded
him, and took his wife to himself; 
<t lang="es"><st n="1161">Entonces</st> <st n="2501">José</st> 
<st n="1326">despertó</st> <st n="575">de</st> su <st n="5258">sueño</st>, 
e <st n="4160">hizo</st> <st n="5613">como</st> el <st n="32">ángel</st> 
del <st n="2962">Señor</st> <st c="4367,846">le ordenó</st>, 
<st n="2532">y</st> <st n="3880">tomó</st> a <st n="846">su</st> 
<st n="1135">esposa</st> consigo; </t>
<sv num="25" id="Mateo-1-25"/>
and didn´t know her sexually until
she had brought forth her firstborn son. He named him Jesus.
<t lang="es"><st n="2532">y</st> </t>
<rb lang="es"><st c="1097,846,3756">no la conoció</st><rf><citebib id="WEB"/> 
dice `no la conoció sexualmente,´ <citebib id="DieBibel"/>, 
<citebib id="Peshitta"/> y <citebib id="KJV2003"/> dicen `no la conoció.´
</rf></rb>
<t lang="es"> <st c="2193,3739">hasta</st> que ella <st c="5088">dio a luz</st>
a <st n="846">su</st> <st n="4416">primer</st> <st n="5207">hijo</st>. </t>
<rb lang="es"><st c="2532"></st>Él<rf><citebib id="Peshitta"/> dice `ella.´</rf></rb>
<t lang="es"> lo <st c="2564,846,3686">llamó</st> <st n="2424">Jesús</st>. </t>
</cm>
<cm>
</cm>
</sc>
<sc num="2" id="Mateo-2">
<cm>
<t lang="es"></t>
<sv num="1" id="Mateo-2-1"/>
Now when Jesus was born in Bethlehem of Judea in the days of Herod
the king, behold, 
<t lang="es"><st n="1161">Cuando</st> <st n="2424">Jesús</st> 
<st n="1080">nació</st> <st n="1722">en</st> <st n="965">Belén</st> de 
<st n="2449">Judea</st>, <st n="1722">en</st> <st n="2250">días</st> del 
<st c="2264,935">rey Herodes</st>,
<st c="2400"/> <st n="3854">vinieron</st> </t>
<rb>wise men
<t lang="es"><st n="3097">hombres sabios</st></t><rf>The word for 
